        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "refactor(telegram): persist plugin state in sqlite",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Move remaining Telegram plugin-local state off JSON sidecars and into plugin-state SQLite: update offsets, sticker cache, sent-message cache, thread bindings, and message dispatch dedupe.\n- Keep legacy JSON handling in startup/doctor migration plans only; runtime update-offset and thread-binding paths now read/write SQLite state directly instead of maintaining fallback files.\n- Extend plugin-state imports so Telegram update-offset migration can replace stale SQLite rows with newer compatible legacy sidecar values before archiving, and detect orphaned Telegram account sidecars from filenames.\n- Add startup guard coverage for Telegram update-offset, sticker-cache, and thread-binding sidecars so read-only commands still trigger migration when needed.\n\n## Verification\nBehavior addressed: Telegram plugin-local cache/state sidecars migrate to plugin-state SQLite without runtime JSON fallback paths.\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/update-offset-store.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/thread-bindings.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/message-dispatch-dedupe.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/sticker-cache.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/state-migrations.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/message-cache.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/token.test.ts src/cli/program/config-guard.test.ts src/commands/doctor-state-migrations.test.ts\nEvidence after fix: 3 Vitest shards passed; CLI config guard 26 tests, doctor migrations 35 tests, Telegram extension 220 tests.\nObserved result after fix: legacy Telegram JSON sidecars are represented as migration plans, runtime state uses plugin-state SQLite, and newer compatible update-offset sidecars can replace stale SQLite rows during migration.\nWhat was not tested: no new live Telegram/Crabbox run for this cleanup commit; earlier PR validation covered real install/migration behavior.\n\nAdditional checks:\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/root.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.json src/channels/plugins/types.core.ts src/infra/state-migrations.ts src/commands/doctor-state-migrations.test.ts src/cli/program/config-guard.ts src/cli/program/config-guard.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/update-offset-store.ts extensions/telegram/src/update-offset-store.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/thread-bindings.ts extensions/telegram/src/thread-bindings.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/state-migrations.ts extensions/telegram/src/state-migrations.test.ts\n- git diff --check\n- /Users/steipete/Projects/agent-skills/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local",
